  </oversight_info>
  <brief_summary>
    <textblock>
      The purpose of the trial is to evaluate the safety of microplasmin as well as its ability to
      open blocked arteries to the brain in patients with acute stroke when given into the artery
      at the site of the blockage.
    </textblock>
  </brief_summary>
  <detailed_description>
    <textblock>
      Patients with angiographically documented acute intracranial vertebrobasilar artery occlusion
      presenting within 24 hours of neurological symptom onset will be enrolled into this
      open-label trial. During study drug administration, angiograms will be repeated at regular
      intervals to determine degree of clot lysis.
    </textblock>
  </detailed_description>
